plex relationship with the Egyptian state, the religious establishment, and the French government, Hussam R. Ahmed reveals modern Egypt's cultural influence in the Arab and Islamic world within the various structural changes and political processes of the parliamentary period. Ahmed offers both a history of modern state formation, revealing how the Egyptian state came to hold such a strong grip over culture and education—and a compelling examination of the life of the country's most renowned intellectual.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aEducation and statezEgyptxHistoryy20th century. 0aEducation ministerszEgyptvBiography. 0aIntellectualszEgyptvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh  aTaha Hussein.  aadab.  acultural history.  ademocracy.  ahumanism.  ainstitutional history.  anahda.  aparliamentary Egypt.  asocial history.  auniversity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362796340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503627963423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503627963/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles